node.text:
Stuart demonstrates exactly how to use a HAIMER Presetter to get offsets. This can be done while the CNC Machine is cutting chips and making money. When the machine is ready to change jobs, you simply load the new tools, while all offsets are transferred to the machine automatically. This allows for a much shorter set up time and keeps the CNC Machine making money.

node.text:
MONSTER TOOLS… Kennametal Chevron Long Edge Milling Cutter + Kennametal HARVI ULTRA 8X in Titanium.

The MRR can’t be beat. Some of these tools are 3.0 Dia and have an Axial Depth of 9.0+ which is absolutely insane. Just complete Rigidity… Huge companies like Boeing etc… usually have multiple tools loaded and are rotating inserts on other replacement tools while the machine runs non-stop.

Machine Shown: Makino (T Series)

node.text:
Preparing vises for table installation and using the bar trick to save time with alignment... 

We have found that using a bar for multiple vise alignment speeds up the process. Before tightening the vises to the table we clamp both vises to the bar which puts them in alignment to each other... then we align the entire combination as a single unit... this is especially helpful when loading 4 or more vises perfectly to a table. Once everything is close... then you unclamp the bar and simply work each individual vise into perfection with your Mitutoyo Indicator.

node.text:
Trevor testing out the annealing process on our new Trumpf TruMark Station 3000…

During the engraving process, the laser was engraving down into the metal, but on the annealing process, the laser is heating the metal up to where it’s changing colors. 

It’s crazy how smooth it comes out…

node.text:
Laser Engraving a piece of Stainless Steel…

Trevor testing out our new Trumpf TruMark Station 3000.

With many companies requiring laser part marking on their prints… We wanted to bring in a versatile laser marker. This specific Trumpf TruMark comes with a 20 watt infrared fiber laser. It can engrave in white and black… and at different depths, it can mark by annealing and also ablation.
